      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td style="padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-bottom:20px"><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">A new phenomenon called &#147;EBay drop-off stores&#148; is sweeping the globe. EBay estimates that sales through <strong>drop-off stores may reach $10 Billion per year, which would yield $700 Million in revenues to eBay </strong>. (NashvilleCityPaper.com, 03/10/04 )</font></p>
          <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">EBay drop-off stores are &#147;tapping into an untouched market: people who want to sell on eBay but don't have the time, or don't want the hassle of photographing their items, listing them online, answering buyers' questions and shipping what's sold.&#148; ( Miami Herald.com 04/31/04 )</font></p>
          <ul>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Orbit Drop, Inc. (OBDP:PK) (http://www.orbitdrop.com) is a &#147;EBay drop-off&#148; company with 4 company owned stores in Texas , 1 in Paris France and currently offering franchising.</strong></font></li>
          </ul>          <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>OBDP </strong> is more than just the average &#147;EBay drop-off&#148; company. <strong>OBDP </strong> has created multiple revenue streams to form a solid foundation for the <strong>Company </strong> to offer franchising and future expansion. These revenue streams will be apparent as <strong>OBDP </strong> updates its financials. </font></p>
          <ol>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">US and International Company owned stores </font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">US and International franchising and licensing </font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The purchase of Success Direct TV and its revenues </font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Private Labeling </font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Drop-off store acquisitions</font></li>
          </ol>          <h1><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Recent Press Releases </font></h1>
          <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">02/28/05<strong> Orbit Drop Receives First of five Shipments of Von Dutch<br>
          </strong>02/25/05<strong> Orbit Drop Maps out Revenues and Advertising Through Subsidiary<br>
</strong>02/14/05<strong> OBDP Signs Potential Area Developers<br>
</strong>02/11/05<strong> OBDP Acquires AuctionGateway.com<br>
</strong>02/11/05<strong> OBDP engages The iFranchise Group<br>
</strong>01/31/05<strong> OBDP Acquires Success Direct TV<br>
</strong>01/31/05<strong> OBDP Signs Lease for Company Drop-off Store in Paris , France </strong></font></p>
          <ul>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>OBDP </strong>'s first shipment of 50,000 out of 200,000 pieces of Von Dutch hats, t-shirts and jeans has a retail value of $1,250,000. </font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>OBDP </strong>'s acquisition Success Direct TV makes sense because of the visibility of the products and the international advertising expertise. This will only help <strong>OBDP </strong>'s visibility and on-line marketing revenues and assets. </font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>OBDP </strong>'s is currently taking applications for area developers and franchisees. </font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The iFranchise Group prides itself on client selectivity and has worked with such companies as <strong>Ace Hardware, Chevron, McDonald's and many more. ( <a href='http://www.znetmail.biz/080E181D0117321F1D1C19170B5C1D00150E44434341460E410E400E4044404B4341420E08.aspx'>www.ifranchise.net </a>) </strong></font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>OBDP </strong>'s subsidiary Success Direct TV generated $4.7 Million in revenues last year and estimates about $10 Million for 2005 </font></li>
            <li><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>OBDP </strong> Dunn &amp; Bradstreet number is 170460625. This number allows potential investors to monitor the financial growth and expansion of the Company</font></li>
          </ul>          <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>OBDP </strong>'s management anticipates a banner year through franchise sales, corporate-owned store revenues and sales from direct marketing.</font><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style=''><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>          </td>
